Project RollUp — future agent quick guide

Use the root-level site files.
Do not assume /web is the live app.
If the user mentions public_html, treat it as the packaging/output folder.

Main goals already implemented:
- green CRT news UI
- 100+ headline guarantee
- deduped source-diverse feed
- bottom-right location globe
- fact-based 400-word write-ups
- responsive desktop/tablet focus, globe hidden on mobile

Key files:
- app.py
- index.html
- script.js
- styles.css
- public_html/ (packaged copy when requested)

Before shipping:
- run python3 -m py_compile app.py
- run node --check script.js
- ensure 100 headlines still render
- ensure globe hides below mobile breakpoint
- ensure summary modal opens/closes cleanly

Recent pitfall:
- a stray shell fragment once got left in app.py; always verify syntax after edits.